<!-- STORY EDITORIAL -->
<section class="section editorial" id="story" style="padding:0">
  <div class="editorial-grid">
    <div class="editorial-img reveal">
      <img width="1200" height="800" loading="lazy" src="{{ 'elehub-selected-024.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Visitors hiking through dense jungle alongside elephant">
    </div>
    <div class="editorial-text reveal d2">
      <span class="sec-label">Our Story</span>
      <div class="sec-title">Born from<br><em>compassion.</em></div>
      <div class="sec-rule"></div>
      <p class="sec-body">
        In 2016, our founders witnessed the suffering elephants endured in Thailand's tourism industry — chained, forced to perform, used as tools. Two rescued elephants, <strong>Boon-Me</strong> and <strong>Thu-Meh</strong>, became the heart of everything we do.
        <br><br>
        Today, across camps in Chiang Mai and Chonburi Province, we care for over 20 rescued elephants working alongside Karen Hill Tribe mahouts whose families have lived with elephants for generations.
      </p>
      <a href="#ethics" class="btn-ghost-dark" style="margin-top:34px;display:inline-block">Our Six Promises</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

