<!-- ETHICS -->
<section class="section ethics-section" id="ethics">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="ethics-header reveal">
      <span class="sec-label">Our Ethics</span>
      <div class="sec-title">Six Promises We <em>Never Break</em></div>
      <div class="sec-rule"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="ethics-grid">
      <div class="ethics-item reveal d1">
        <span class="ethics-icon">✕</span>
        <div class="ethics-name">No Riding. Ever.</div>
        <p class="ethics-text">Riding causes permanent spinal damage. We refuse every request — no exceptions, no compromises, under any circumstances.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ethics-item reveal d2">
        <span class="ethics-icon">✕</span>
        <div class="ethics-name">No Performances</div>
        <p class="ethics-text">Elephants are not entertainers. Ours live at their own pace, on their own terms — as nature intended.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ethics-item reveal d3">
        <span class="ethics-icon">✕</span>
        <div class="ethics-name">Zero Force</div>
        <p class="ethics-text">Bathing, feeding, walking — all activities follow each elephant's own mood and instinct. Nothing is ever forced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ethics-item reveal d1">
        <span class="ethics-icon">✕</span>
        <div class="ethics-name">No Bull Hooks</div>
        <p class="ethics-text">Our mahouts build relationships grounded in trust and care — not dominance or control instruments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ethics-item reveal d2">
        <span class="ethics-icon">○</span>
        <div class="ethics-name">Habitat Protection</div>
        <p class="ethics-text">40+ acres of protected forest. We grow elephant food on-site, actively reforest land and support anti-poaching efforts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ethics-item reveal d3">
        <span class="ethics-icon">○</span>
        <div class="ethics-name">Community First</div>
        <p class="ethics-text">Partnered with Karen Hill Tribe mahouts to create dignified livelihoods and preserve generations of traditional elephant knowledge.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

